section.def:
carcass
                (屠體) means the whole or any part of a carcass of
            slaughtered poultry;

edible
                (可食用) means suitable and fit for human
            consumption;

employee
                (僱員) includes every person working in a poultry export factory, whether or not employed by the
            licensee;

export
                (出口、輸出) means
            to take or send out of Hong Kong by any means;

inspector
                (督察) means a public officer appointed as an
            inspector under section 17 of the Ordinance;

licence
                (牌照) means a licence granted under paragraph (1)
            of regulation 5;

licensee
                (持牌人) means a person who holds a licence granted
            to him and also means a deputy appointed under regulation 10;

paragraph.content:
to
                    line
                    containers in which carcasses or poultry products are packed;

bear a number which shall appear on every licence which may thereafter be
                    granted under these regulations in respect of the premises to which the licence
                    relates;

leaves Hong Kong without first complying with
                    subparagraph
                    (a) of paragraph (1);

fails to appoint a deputy under
                    subparagraph
                    (b) of paragraph (1) when so required by the Director;

suitable office accommodation together with adequate furniture,
                lighting
                and heating for such accommodation;

the Food Adulteration (Metallic Contamination) Regulations (Cap. 132 sub. leg. V);
                (E.R. 3 of
                2023)
